Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @boiled water{450%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock paste{20%g} and stir well to combine - this is your chicken stock.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat. TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal #saucepan{} and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} later.

Once hot, add the @British chicken breast{260%g}(diced) and fry until browned all over ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and onion to the chicken and fry until the onion starts to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g} to the pan, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in your chicken stock and bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

When the risotto has finished cooking, remove it from the oven and stir through the @butter{10%g}, @peas{120%g} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the chicken and chorizo risotto between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian style cheese to finish. Enjoy!